	############################################################################
	Project Title
	PACKT - Verification of UI Elements 
	############################################################################
	
	a.Automation software and reportingÂ 
	Packt is web application. I have chosen Selenium for Automation purpose and Java as
	the language with Cucumber. It uses Gherkin langauge which is easy to understand for 
	all the stakeholders.
	For execution part, JUnit is used and Extent Reports for generating reports.
	
	############################################################################
	b.Installation & Execution Steps
	
	1.Download Zip file and Unzip it to your Workspace directory
	2.Install Java and Eclipse[prefer latest one] 
	3.Open Eclipse > File > Import projects existing Workspace directory
	4.Expand and Open > com.packt.stepdefinitions.TestRunnerPackt.java file 
	5.Run as > Junit Test 
	6.After execution Report will be generated - under Packt/reports/PacktExtentReportResults.html
	
	############################################################################
	c.Other information
	
	Folder Structure >
	1.Testdata is under src/main/resources/TestDataFiles/PacktTestdata.xls
	
	There are four scenarios and each scenario uses sheet.
	User can change this file according to different testdata as when required
	
	Scenario 1 Sheet - includes ElementName,Locators(with locator type as CSS),CSS Value,Color and Text 
	It takes these values as expected values and compare with actual values
	For this scenario,I have passed locator address but we can achive this using Page Object Model as enhancements 
	
	Scenario 2 Sheet - includes Menu Name > SubMenu Name > Menu Item 
	It helps to navigate using top navigation bar
	[for eg Browse > Web Development >Flask ]
	
	Scenario 3 Sheet - includes Element No Sequence	and Carosuel Element Name
	It helps to click on carosuel element according to sequence given in sheet
	
	Scenario 4 Sheet - includes Search Criteria	and Search Criteria	Values
	It helps to apply filters while Searching product using values
	
	
	2.Config files is under src/main/resources/Configs/Configs.properties file
	
	It contains URL, Browser , Testdata file name, Username and password details
	User can change this file according to different configurations
	
	3.Feature file is under resources/Features/Packt_UI_Functionalities.feature file
	
	It contains four scenarios written in Gherkin.
	
	4.Extend Reports will get generated under - Packt/PacktExtentReportResults.html
	
	It will shows Pass/Fail Testcase with Total Steps, Time taken
	
	
	